texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: I've talked about some of my experiences with altering my diet on Twitter and many people have asked about my experiences with keto so far. Note that I don't call it "the keto diet" because it's much more than a diet: it's a lifestyle  change. Sure, you alter what you eat, but you begin to think differently about how you fuel your body.

texts.label: section_header
texts.orig: What is keto?
texts.text: What is keto?

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: When you adopt a keto lifestyle, you change what fuel is used primarily in your body. It's a high fat, moderate protein, low carbohydrate approach.
texts.text: When you adopt a keto lifestyle, you change what fuel is used primarily in your body. It's a high fat, moderate protein, low carbohydrate approach.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: Low carbohydrate diets are not new. They were studied heavily in the early 1900's as a  potential remedy for epilepsy . Doctors noticed that patients who fasted had fewer problems, but the patients couldn't maintain fasting for extended periods. Once they put the patients on a high fat diet and the body went into ketosis (where it burns fat for fuel), the patients had fewer problems.
texts.text: Low carbohydrate diets are not new. They were studied heavily in the early 1900's as a  potential remedy for epilepsy . Doctors noticed that patients who fasted had fewer problems, but the patients couldn't maintain fasting for extended periods. Once they put the patients on a high fat diet and the body went into ketosis (where it burns fat for fuel), the patients had fewer problems.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: These diets are still used today for children and adults with seizure disorders and other brain-related conditions. To learn more about these patients and how fat works in your body, read Dr. Mark Hyman's  Eat Fat Get Thin . He provides tons of easy to understand reasons why a high fat diet is better and he provides links to hundreds of studies and publications about it.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: Hold on for a moment.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: As a friend explained to me, doing keto the right way is like getting the right octane gasoline from a reputable gas station. It burns clean and make your car run well. You can choose a different octane or choose a shady gas station and your car will still run, but it might make noise, run slower, or send you to the mechanic more often.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: People often talk about "dirty" and "clean" keto. If you focus purely on your carbohydrate target and use any foods you want to fill up your calories from fat, you will end up in ketosis. However, some of these foods will slow your weight loss progress (if that's your goal) and they may rob some of the additional keto health benefits from you.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: First, let's talk about weight loss. You can check Reddit's r/keto  for some amazing weight loss stories. People have loss hundreds of pounds and kept it off!
texts.text: First, let's talk about weight loss. You can check Reddit's r/keto  for some amazing weight loss stories. People have loss hundreds of pounds and kept it off!

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: I started around 195 lbs (88.5 kg) and I am 6'1" (1.85 m) tall. After starting keto, my weight  increased  (as did my blood pressure). I was frustrated as the food change was difficult and I felt like I was doing a lot of work for nothing. Online forums reassured me that this was part of the process and that I should keep pushing.
texts.text: I started around 195 lbs (88.5 kg) and I am 6'1" (1.85 m) tall. After starting keto, my weight  increased  (as did my blood pressure). I was frustrated as the food change was difficult and I felt like I was doing a lot of work for nothing. Online forums reassured me that this was part of the process and that I should keep pushing.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: So I kept pushing and stayed with it. Around the 3-4 week mark, the weight slowly began to come down. Within two months, I was down to 180 (81.6 kg). Within three months, I was at 174 (78.9 kg) and realized I didn't want to be that thin! After increasing my fat intake a bit more, I'm able to hover around 180 lbs and that's very comfortable for me.

After increasing my fat intake a bit more, I'm able to hover around 180 lbs and that's very comfortable for me.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: Even at 180 lbs, I looked different. Some of the troublesome fat that I dealt with (love handles!) shrank some. I moved from a 36 in most pants down to a 34 (and a 32 in some).
texts.text: Even at 180 lbs, I looked different. Some of the troublesome fat that I dealt with (love handles!) shrank some. I moved from a 36 in most pants down to a 34 (and a 32 in some).

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: The best part about all of this is that my body stays between 178-182 lbs reliably without needing to take any drastic action. It is easy to maintain.

texts.label: section_header
texts.orig: What are the health benefits?
texts.text: What are the health benefits?

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: I've had mild high blood pressure for a few years and I was taking medication (lisinopril) to reduce it. The medicine worked fairly well and and kept me in a better range. However, I had spells where I would stand from sitting and I felt like I was going to pass out. I felt tired more often and felt lightheaded after working out.
texts.text: I've had mild high blood pressure for a few years and I was taking medication (lisinopril) to reduce it. The medicine worked fairly well and and kept me in a better range. However, I had spells where I would stand from sitting and I felt like I was going to pass out. I felt tired more often and felt lightheaded after working out.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: I've also had asthma for years and I've taken various medications (montelukast, albeuterol, olopatadine, flonase) to deal with that and my seasonal allergies. My asthma has put me in the ER more than once.
texts.text: I've also had asthma for years and I've taken various medications (montelukast, albeuterol, olopatadine, flonase) to deal with that and my seasonal allergies. My asthma has put me in the ER more than once.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: After about four months of keto, my lightheaded spells got worse and my doctor told me to stop taking blood pressure medication. I watched my blood pressure closely and found that I no longer needed medication for it!  (That was one medication I was really glad to throw away.)
texts.text: After about four months of keto, my lightheaded spells got worse and my doctor told me to stop taking blood pressure medication. I watched my blood pressure closely and found that I no longer needed medication for it!  (That was one medication I was really glad to throw away.)

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: I'm about 8 months in now and I was able to stop taking all allergy and asthma medications about a month ago. This really makes me think that something was in my diet that was causing me harm.

Too much alcohol will stunt your progress towards weight loss and other health benefits.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: Many people talk about the "keto flu", which is a period that lasts anywhere from a few days to a week where you feel pretty terrible. Your energy level will drop, exercising will be difficult, and you will be irritable. This is the period where your body has exhausted its supply of easily accessible glucose and it's changing gears to burn fat.

texts.text: What happens when I eat bad things?

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: This happens to all of us. I was two months in on keto when Thanksgiving arrived. That's a big holiday in the US where we generally eat a lot, and a lot of what we eat is carbs. Some potatoes, pumpkin pie, and beer tempted me and I woke up the next morning feeling awful. My stomach cramped and I felt nauseated.
texts.text: This happens to all of us. I was two months in on keto when Thanksgiving arrived. That's a big holiday in the US where we generally eat a lot, and a lot of what we eat is carbs. Some potatoes, pumpkin pie, and beer tempted me and I woke up the next morning feeling awful. My stomach cramped and I felt nauseated.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: Many people suggested getting right back into keto with high fat foods and exercise. I persevered with that and felt better by the end of the day.
texts.text: Many people suggested getting right back into keto with high fat foods and exercise. I persevered with that and felt better by the end of the day.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: If you do make a bad choice and spike your blood sugar, your body will crave more sugar and put you into a keto-busting spiral. Your digestive system biome that changed to work with a high-fat diet will get confused with a sudden influx of carbs and it will cramp. However, if you get back on track quickly, those problems will subside.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: Remember that this is a choice  you make  for  your body.  Don't ever say "I can't eat that" because your brain will see your lifestyle change as limitation. I usually say "Thank you, but I don't eat that" or "I love what you made, but that's not something I eat."

texts.text: What do I do when I get invited out for dinner?

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: This is probably the toughest part. What do you do if you get asked to go to dinner or if you're on the road and you need to get food? You don't really notice how much of the American diet is made from carbohydrates until you start avoiding them.  They are everywhere.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: Vegetarians and vegans have a similar problem here. Try to look at the menu ahead of time and figure out the things that you can eat.
texts.text: Vegetarians and vegans have a similar problem here. Try to look at the menu ahead of time and figure out the things that you can eat.
